#### WINDOWS ###
Best to run code in VS Code

req install verification:
  python --version
  pip --version

inside the project folder, run:
  pip install flask
  python -m venv venv
  venv\Scripts\activate   # On Windows

from project folder, open terminal, run:
  python app.py

once you see "* Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000/"
follow the hyperlink to the browser

demo accounts:
Admin	      admin	  password
Instructor	alice	  password
Student	    sarah	  password

in terminal type CTRL + C to stop the local server

### MacOS ###
Best to run code in VS Code

req install verification:
  python3 --version
  pip3 --version

inside the project folder, run:
  pip3 install flask
  python3 -m venv venv
  source venv/bin/activate   # On MacOS

from project folder, open terminal, run:
  python3 app.py

once you see "* Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000/"
follow the hyperlink to the browser

demo accounts:
Admin	      admin	  password
Instructor	alice	  password
Student	    sarah	  password

in terminal type CTRL + C to stop the local server
